content: PSQL was included with some purchases of Dell, Acer, Sony, and other computers. However, the software is no longer supported. It was originally developed by UPEK, a company that merged with AuthenTec. AuthenTec discontinued PSQL as well as all of its other identity management products.
NOTE: PSQL is supported for only Windows 2000, XP. and Vista.

description: Archive created by Protector Suite QL (PSQL), a program that secures personal files using fingerprint technology; stores user files and encrypts them with the user's fingerprint, which is collected from a sensor device attached to the computer.
